verbose_text: Notably MS patients showed significantly lower levels of eicosapentaenoic acid (EPA) in erythrocyte phospholipids, as well as lower docosahexaenoic acid (DHA) concentration in adipose tissue compared to healthy individuals [XREF_BIBR].
